# =============================================================================
# Healthspend v1.0 - Open Source .gitignore
# For Cloudflare Pages deployment with GitHub integration
# =============================================================================

# Build outputs (never commit built code)
dist/
web/dist/
target/
*.o
*.a
*.so
.cargo/

# Dependencies (use lock files instead)
node_modules/
.npm/
__pycache__/
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/

# Data files (CSVs and databases regenerated via build pipeline)
*.csv
*.db
*.db-*
*.db-journal
scraper/*.db*

# EXCEPTION: Audit data is tracked for regulatory compliance
!web/public/audit_data.db
!web/public/favicon.ico

# Temporary/local files
*.log
*.tmp
*.temp
*.pid
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Python cache
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/

# IDEs
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.project
.classpath

# Environment variables (CRITICAL: never commit credentials)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# OS-specific
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT ARCHITECTURE: Cloudflare Pages + GitHub
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
# 1. You push code to GitHub (public, open-source)
# 2. Cloudflare Pages hook detects push to main
# 3. Cloudflare runs build: `cd web && npm run build`
# 4. Build output goes to web/dist/
# 5. Cloudflare deploys ONLY web/dist/ to edge
# 6. End users see only the built website, not source files
#
# RESULT: GitHub repo is public & transparent (open source), but the deployed
# website only exposes what's in web/dist/ (built output).
#
# =============================================================================

# Clinical Data Nodes (INTENTIONALLY INCLUDED FOR DEPLOYMENT)
# 
# These 5,400+ HTML files represent healthcare facility visibility data
# drawn from CMS public disclosure requirements and scientific research.
# 
# They are:
# - Committed to GitHub (open-source transparency)
# - Built into web/dist/ for Cloudflare deployment
# - Public climate/regulatory data (not sensitive)
# - Core to the project's healthcare transparency mission
#
# DO NOT EXCLUDE THESE—they are essential project data
#
!web/public/visibility/
!web/public/api/v1/
!web/public/sitemap.xml
!web/public/media-brief-2026.html
!web/public/transparency-2026.html
!web/public/transparency-index.html
!web/public/mri-variation-report.html
